  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.10.18-unstable\r\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 20.04\r\nCommit hash : f0328f241b7c3def217b0c2dce1a1b297f979a37  (20220413)\r\n\r\nRaspberry Pi, 8GB, 1TB Samsung SSD\r\n\r\nI installed prometheus/grafana about a month ago and have been watching my geth node.  About 4 times now I have seen geth engage in sustained, fairly heavy (20-30 MB/s) disk read activity, for quite long periods of time (5-9 hours).\r\n\r\nIf this is a feature I am curious what geth is doing.  If this is a bug/issue, I would be happy to provide more information if I can.\r\n\r\n![Screenshot 2022-04-20 193717](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/30419645/164378034-850a59ee-224c-411e-a739-da0eed855163.png)\r\n\r\n![Screenshot 2022-04-20 193753](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/30419645/164378522-2a43c107-4fcb-4528-9da9-3d9f4ef65745.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n",
